Defendant Alexander I Siniard in court with Attorney Parker Charles Mathers.  Defendant Alexander I Siniard in custody.  Francesco Mineo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter here for a Plea/Sentencing.  As to Plea:  AS TO COUNT #1:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty.  Judgment of conviction entered.

AS TO COUNTS #2 AND #3:    Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered case dismissed and read-in for the purposes of sentencing.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess any gun or other firearms. 
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.  

Court advised defendant if he is not a citizen of the United States of America, that upon a plea of guilty or no contest for this offense, he could be deported, excluded from admission to his country, or denied naturalization under federal law.  
Court advised that the defendant will have to provide a DNA sample, to the Wisconsin State Crime Laboratory for DNA testing and pay a DNA surcharge.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by: Simone Seitz.

The Court imposed the following sentence:   
AS TO COUNT #1:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be THIRTY-SIX (36) months CONSECUTIVE to 15CF512.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for TWELVE (12) months with credit for EIGHTEEN (18) days time served.  Defendant shall serve TWENTY-FOUR (24) months on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  

The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  The Court is to be notified after 30 days of completion.  Once Court is notified and approval granted, the Defendant can be released and remaining incarceration balance can be added to extended supervision time.
The defendant IS eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court is to be notified after 30 days of completion.  Once Court is notified and approval is granted, the Defendant can be released and remaining incarceration balance can be added to extended supervision time.  

The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Urine screens to ensure compliance; Absolute Sobriety
 - Interlock Device for 24 months;
 - Operating Privileges suspended for 36 months TO COMMENCE UPON ELIGIBILITY TO REINSTATE LICENSE;
 - Pay fine in the amount of $1,200 plus costs, surcharges and fees;
 - Inform any and all medical personnel of drug addiction;
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements.  Fees are to be taken out of bail on deposit.  Balance of bail can be mailed back to surety.   

Filed,
Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
